        <item>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <actionDate>2015-04-16</actionDate>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2015-04-28T15:05:51Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Steve Gleason Act of 2015</b></p> <p>This bill amends title XVIII (Medicare) of the Social Security Act to cover as durable medical equipment any eye tracking and gaze interaction accessories for speech generating devices furnished to individuals with a demonstrated medical need for them.</p> <p>Payment for speech generating devices or accessories furnished during FY2015-FY2018 shall be made on a rental basis, or in a lump-sum amount for the purchase of the item, without a cap on the amount.</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2015-04-16T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
